SIMPLE: incisive
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Incisive
<hw>In*ci"sive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>incisif</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Having the quality of incising, cutting, or
penetrating, as with a sharp instrument; cutting;</def>
<specif>hence,</specif> <def>sharp; acute; sarcastic; biting;
trenchant.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧An <xex>incisive</xex>, high voice.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And her <qex>incisive</qex> smile accrediting⟦br⟧
That treason of false witness in my blush.</q> <rj><qau>Mrs.
Browning.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the incisors;
incisor; <as>as, the <ex>incisive</ex> bones, the
premaxillaries</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Clearly and succinctly stated, with penetrating
insight into the issue at hand; <as>as, an <ex>incisive</ex>
comment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>incisiveness</ent>⟦br⟧
